251
00:10:14,781 --> 00:10:16,782
I can't rinse if there
are dishes piled on both sides.

252
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:18,483
I'll try and remember that.

253
00:10:18,535 --> 00:10:21,820
You'd think a guy with your
memory wouldn't have to try.

254
00:10:21,872 --> 00:10:23,873
- All right, let's hear it.
- Hear what?

255
00:10:23,957 --> 00:10:25,507
- The list.
- What list?

256
00:10:25,592 --> 00:10:26,792
Of things I do
that annoy you.

257
00:10:26,843 --> 00:10:28,260
- I don't have a list.
- Everyone has a list.

258
00:10:28,328 --> 00:10:29,845
- Do you have a list?
- This isn't about my list.

259
00:10:29,930 --> 00:10:31,163
This is about your list.

260
00:10:31,214 --> 00:10:33,132
No, it's about yours
because I just told you

261
00:10:33,183 --> 00:10:34,499
everything that's on mine.

262
00:10:34,551 --> 00:10:36,852
You're telling me
that the most meticulous woman

263
00:10:36,937 --> 00:10:39,004
on the upper West Side
only has a list of two?

264
00:10:39,055 --> 00:10:40,689
- That's not fair.
- No, what's not fair

265
00:10:40,774 --> 00:10:42,441
is you making this
all about me.

266
00:10:42,508 --> 00:10:44,560
I might not be perfect,
but neither are you.

267
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:46,612
So, excuse me, I have more
important things to do

268
00:10:46,679 --> 00:10:50,449
than talk about where
I left my coffee cup.

269
00:10:50,516 --> 00:10:51,984
- Fair?
- Fair.

270
00:10:52,035 --> 00:10:55,704
- Fair?
- Yes, fair.

271
00:10:55,789 --> 00:10:58,457
I didn't even like playing
nice in the sandbox.

272
00:10:58,524 --> 00:10:59,541
Someone has better sand toys,

273
00:10:59,626 --> 00:11:00,826
you take 'em.
Exactly.

274
00:11:00,877 --> 00:11:02,361
And you don't ask
Bolshoi ballerinas

275
00:11:02,412 --> 00:11:03,579
to dance the tango.

276
00:11:03,663 --> 00:11:05,224
That would indeed
be blasphemy.

277
00:11:05,298 --> 00:11:06,582
If Jessica wants compromise,

278
00:11:06,666 --> 00:11:09,335
she should hire a mediator,
not a gladiator.

279
00:11:09,386 --> 00:11:11,387
Except Jessica
doesn't want compromise.

280
00:11:11,471 --> 00:11:13,839
She wants a stone-cold killer to
do one thing and one thing only.

281
00:11:13,890 --> 00:11:15,257
And what is that?

282
00:11:15,342 --> 00:11:17,893
Not to lock client allocations
till Harvey lands Samsung.

283
00:11:17,978 --> 00:11:19,228
Then give me an order.

284
00:11:19,312 --> 00:11:22,231
Your order is to not let
my inner gladiator

285
00:11:22,315 --> 00:11:24,049
get past my outer negotiator.

286
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:26,068
That's not
gonna be easy, Louis.

287
00:11:26,152 --> 00:11:27,872
You're like the Hulk--
once you get enraged,

288
00:11:27,887 --> 00:11:29,321
there's no going back.

289
00:11:29,389 --> 00:11:30,722
Though your description
of both my temperament

290
00:11:30,774 --> 00:11:32,942
and physique is accurate,
the one thing that I have

291
00:11:33,026 --> 00:11:35,244
on my side is that I have
no personal animus

292
00:11:35,328 --> 00:11:37,329
against the other side.

293
00:11:44,070 --> 00:11:46,038
Nesbitt.

294
00:11:46,089 --> 00:11:47,957
Litt.

295
00:11:48,041 --> 00:11:50,075
I see you're wearing
your checkered suit

296
00:11:50,126 --> 00:11:51,576
with your crimson power tie.

297
00:11:51,628 --> 00:11:53,212
You see correctly.

298
00:11:53,263 --> 00:11:54,746
Looks like you came
to play hardball.

299
00:11:54,798 --> 00:11:55,998
I didn't come
to play anything.

300
00:11:56,049 --> 00:11:57,749
I came to win.
Well, I'm not here to win.

301
00:11:57,801 --> 00:12:00,219
I'm here to make sure we
hammer out a fair agreement.

302
00:12:00,270 --> 00:12:01,720
And to help you achieve that,

303
00:12:01,771 --> 00:12:03,805
I see you've brought along
Tinker Bell.

304
00:12:04,167 --> 00:12:05,634
You were so scared
of Tinker Bell,

305
00:12:05,659 --> 00:12:07,390
you sent her to Barcelona,
for your cat trial.

306
00:12:07,415 --> 00:12:09,134
During which time,
she worked closely,

307
00:12:09,135 --> 00:12:11,119
with a different senior partner...

308
00:12:11,171 --> 00:12:14,340
again and again.

309
00:12:14,424 --> 00:12:17,226
Don't worry.

310
00:12:17,293 --> 00:12:19,561
Dr. Banner's
not turning green today.

311
00:12:19,629 --> 00:12:22,314
See, whatever you thought was
gonna happen to me here isn't.

312
00:12:22,399 --> 00:12:24,650
So go ahead,
wind me up all you want,

313
00:12:24,734 --> 00:12:26,185
'cause I ain't losing my cool.

314
00:12:26,269 --> 00:12:28,303
Fine.

315
00:12:28,355 --> 00:12:30,656
This is my initial proposal.

316
00:12:35,328 --> 00:12:36,996
Those are letters
I wrote to Mikado.

317
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:39,164
Unopened.

318
00:12:39,249 --> 00:12:40,699
You never read them to her?

319
00:12:40,784 --> 00:12:43,151
- Not a single word.
- You son of a bitch.

320
00:12:43,203 --> 00:12:45,504
You think you can rattle me?
I'm un-rattleable.

321
00:12:45,588 --> 00:12:47,840
Really?

322
00:12:47,924 --> 00:12:50,626
This portrait
that you sent her.

323
00:12:53,380 --> 00:12:55,047
Get out!

324
00:12:55,131 --> 00:12:57,049
- Louis--
- I said go.

325
00:13:02,839 --> 00:13:05,140
Oh, yeah, you and I
are going to war.

326
00:13:05,191 --> 00:13:07,109
Everything's
on the goddamn table!

327
00:13:07,176 --> 00:13:09,778
Including the existing
client list allocations?

328
00:13:09,846 --> 00:13:13,115
Did you hear what I just said?
I said everything!

329
00:13:19,823 --> 00:13:21,690
You son of a bitch.

330
00:13:21,741 --> 00:13:23,292
You knew
I'd come after Samsung.

331
00:13:23,359 --> 00:13:25,661
I knew what suit
you'd be wearing.

332
00:13:25,712 --> 00:13:27,997
I know Tiger Woods
wears red on Sundays.

333
00:13:28,048 --> 00:13:29,331
It doesn't mean
I can beat him.

334
00:13:29,382 --> 00:13:32,301
I'm not going to let you poach
our clients, Harvey.

335
00:13:32,368 --> 00:13:34,202
You poaching our clients
is what led us

336
00:13:34,254 --> 00:13:36,505
to this goddamn merger
in the first place.

337
00:13:36,556 --> 00:13:38,807
That was fair game.
This is bad faith.

338
00:13:38,875 --> 00:13:41,209
Bad faith?
I'm going after Samsung.

339
00:13:41,261 --> 00:13:43,621
I'm not murdering anybody and
lying about it to my partners.

340
00:13:43,646 --> 00:13:45,147
Don't you dare put me in
with them.

341
00:13:45,214 --> 00:13:46,732
You put yourself in
with them.

342
00:13:46,816 --> 00:13:48,383
Speaking of which,
what the hell you still doing

343
00:13:48,435 --> 00:13:49,885
in bed with these people,
Scottie?

344
00:13:49,936 --> 00:13:52,438
As you know, I don't always
have the best judgment

345
00:13:52,522 --> 00:13:53,939
of who I get in bed with.

346
00:13:54,024 --> 00:13:55,607
And as for why I'm still
in business with them--

347
00:13:55,692 --> 00:13:56,825
Let me guess.

348
00:13:56,893 --> 00:13:58,944
You beat me
on the dissolution negotiation,

349
00:13:59,029 --> 00:14:00,162
you get your name on the door.

350
00:14:00,229 --> 00:14:01,330
Yep.
Darby agreed to it

351
00:14:01,397 --> 00:14:03,282
the second
that you pushed him out.

352
00:14:03,366 --> 00:14:05,167
He only did that because
he knew when word got out

353
00:14:05,234 --> 00:14:07,119
that his house was on fire,
he had to do something.

354
00:14:07,203 --> 00:14:09,371
Well, he did.
He put me against you.

355
00:14:09,422 --> 00:14:11,907
And as you just noted,
our house is on fire,

356
00:14:11,958 --> 00:14:13,959
and I'm gonna fight tooth and
nail to put the damn thing out.

357
00:14:14,044 --> 00:14:16,078
You can fight tooth and nail
all you like,

358
00:14:16,129 --> 00:14:18,380
but it's never done a thing
for you against me before.

359
00:14:18,431 --> 00:14:19,882
That's because I always
had something else

360
00:14:19,933 --> 00:14:21,467
on my mind before,

361
00:14:21,551 --> 00:14:24,386
but you've made it clear that
that's never going to happen.

362
00:14:24,437 --> 00:14:25,754
So, if you think
you're gonna win this time,

363
00:14:25,805 --> 00:14:27,523
you've got
another thing coming.

364
00:14:27,590 --> 00:14:28,941
Say what you want, Scottie.

365
00:14:29,025 --> 00:14:30,559
I'm going in there,
and you're not gonna stop me.

366
00:14:33,813 --> 00:14:35,147
I'm afraid I already did.

367
00:14:35,231 --> 00:14:36,782
Client list just got locked.

368
00:14:36,866 --> 00:14:38,767
So you can go in there
and give it a shot,

369
00:14:38,818 --> 00:14:39,985
but they're never gonna sign
with a guy

370
00:14:40,070 --> 00:14:42,788
who just got played
on their front porch.

371
00:14:53,324 --> 00:14:55,307
- Hey.
- Hey.

372
00:14:56,108 --> 00:14:57,836
I got your message.

373
00:14:57,856 --> 00:14:59,190
Thanks for meeting me.

374
00:14:59,274 --> 00:15:01,609
It's not often I get invited
out to hear an apology.

375
00:15:01,660 --> 00:15:05,145
I'm so sorry
I snapped at you.

376
00:15:05,197 --> 00:15:09,316
I got defensive, and when I went
away to think about it,

377
00:15:09,368 --> 00:15:10,535
I came up with why.

378
00:15:10,619 --> 00:15:11,752
Why?

379
00:15:11,820 --> 00:15:15,155
I feel like a guest
in your apartment.

380
00:15:15,207 --> 00:15:17,508
And I think it's because
we spend all of our time

381
00:15:17,593 --> 00:15:19,794
at your place and none
of the time at mine.

382
00:15:19,845 --> 00:15:21,295
Yeah, but I told you,
when I'm at your place,

383
00:15:21,346 --> 00:15:23,831
all I can picture is Tess
in a bedsheet.

384
00:15:23,882 --> 00:15:27,001
I know.
And that's why we're here.

385
00:15:27,052 --> 00:15:29,136
Come on, I want
to show you something.

386
00:15:33,008 --> 00:15:35,026
Louis, we gave you one job,
and you blew it.

387
00:15:35,110 --> 00:15:37,228
How the hell did you screw up
those negotiations?

388
00:15:37,312 --> 00:15:38,512
Screw up? Come on.
What are you talking about?

389
00:15:38,564 --> 00:15:39,530
I got us the corporate jet.

390
00:15:39,615 --> 00:15:41,015
We keep
our first dividend checks,

391
00:15:41,066 --> 00:15:42,233
and they pay
for our new letterhead.

392
00:15:42,317 --> 00:15:43,534
So you know what?

393
00:15:43,619 --> 00:15:45,119
You just put that in your pipe,
and you smoke it.

394
00:15:45,186 --> 00:15:47,538
I don't give a shit
about the goddamn letterhead!

395
00:15:47,623 --> 00:15:48,990
You don't think
I know that?

396
00:15:49,041 --> 00:15:51,742
Nobody cares about
the goddamn letterhead, okay?

397
00:15:51,827 --> 00:15:53,294
Nigel went after Mikado.

398
00:15:53,361 --> 00:15:54,912
What the hell is Mikado?

399
00:15:54,997 --> 00:15:56,414
Not "what," "who."
She's a cat.

400
00:15:56,498 --> 00:15:58,049
He went after your cat?

401
00:15:58,133 --> 00:15:59,467
He went after his cat.

402
00:15:59,534 --> 00:16:03,170
He tortured his cat?

403
00:16:03,222 --> 00:16:06,641
He deprived her
of my letters.

404
00:16:08,510 --> 00:16:12,146
Louis, you lost your shit
during a negotiation

405
00:16:12,213 --> 00:16:14,548
because someone didn't read
your letters to their cat?

406
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:18,319
Harvey, please.
I'm sorry I lost my head.

407
00:16:18,386 --> 00:16:20,721
I don't even remember
signing the agreement.

408
00:16:20,772 --> 00:16:22,990
Well, you did!

409
00:16:23,058 --> 00:16:24,609
And, Louis,
you've been asking Jessica

410
00:16:24,693 --> 00:16:26,226
to give you the ball
instead of me

411
00:16:26,278 --> 00:16:27,245
ever since the day I met you.

412
00:16:27,329 --> 00:16:28,729
Well, she gave it to you,

413
00:16:28,780 --> 00:16:32,333
and you just went and scored
a touchdown for the other team.

414
00:16:43,262 --> 00:16:46,914
Oh, my God.

415
00:16:46,965 --> 00:16:49,016
Your grandmother's apartment.

416
00:16:49,084 --> 00:16:51,469
I still own it.

417
00:16:51,553 --> 00:16:55,523
You kept it
this entire time?

418
00:16:55,590 --> 00:16:57,808
I couldn't rent it.

419
00:16:57,893 --> 00:16:58,976
I couldn't sell it.

420
00:16:59,061 --> 00:17:01,112
I...

421
00:17:01,196 --> 00:17:02,563
Couldn't even come here.

422
00:17:02,614 --> 00:17:04,615
That means the last time
you were here...

423
00:17:04,700 --> 00:17:06,951
We were here.

424
00:17:07,035 --> 00:17:08,619
So you want to move in here?

425
00:17:08,704 --> 00:17:10,621
I want us to move in here.

426
00:17:13,575 --> 00:17:15,409
- Mike--
- Rachel.

427
00:17:15,460 --> 00:17:17,912
I've only ever been here twice,

428
00:17:17,963 --> 00:17:21,115
and both times were with you.

429
00:17:21,166 --> 00:17:23,584
The first time we stood here,

430
00:17:23,635 --> 00:17:26,954
and we pictured
living together.

431
00:17:27,005 --> 00:17:29,507
I'll never forget that.

432
00:17:29,591 --> 00:17:32,977
- Neither will I.
- And the second time...

433
00:17:33,061 --> 00:17:36,147
Was one of the hardest days
of my life,

434
00:17:36,231 --> 00:17:40,017
but I got through it
because we were together.

435
00:17:45,407 --> 00:17:48,993
That's one the sweetest things
I've ever heard.

436
00:17:53,248 --> 00:17:56,617
You don't have to answer
right now, okay?

437
00:17:56,668 --> 00:18:00,421
I just wanted to show you
what we could have.

438
00:18:07,763 --> 00:18:10,047
Goddamn Louis.

439
00:18:10,132 --> 00:18:11,665
Let it go.

440
00:18:11,717 --> 00:18:13,050
Let it go?

441
00:18:13,135 --> 00:18:14,602
You don't say "let it go"

442
00:18:14,669 --> 00:18:16,854
unless you already
didn't let it go.

443
00:18:16,938 --> 00:18:19,473
You gonna take it out on me
for taking it out on him?

444
00:18:19,524 --> 00:18:21,275
At the moment,
we don't have the time.

445
00:18:21,342 --> 00:18:22,810
Good, because
I've already got Mike

446
00:18:22,861 --> 00:18:24,695
looking for ways
to revise the agreement.

447
00:18:24,780 --> 00:18:26,113
The problem
isn't revising it.

448
00:18:26,181 --> 00:18:28,065
The problem is
Louis already signed it.

449
00:18:28,150 --> 00:18:29,784
You're saying
we need to find a loophole.

450
00:18:29,851 --> 00:18:31,035
I am.

451
00:18:31,119 --> 00:18:32,653
Well, if we can't steal
from their clients

452
00:18:32,704 --> 00:18:34,622
and the revenues from new ones
don't count,

453
00:18:34,689 --> 00:18:36,157
what the hell
are we supposed to do?

454
00:18:36,208 --> 00:18:37,792
There's only one thing
to do--

455
00:18:37,859 --> 00:18:39,299
look at the money
we're already owed.

456
00:18:39,327 --> 00:18:41,879
- I don't follow you.
- We're on a cash basis.

457
00:18:41,963 --> 00:18:44,531
We can't count the revenues
we haven't collected yet.

458
00:18:44,583 --> 00:18:47,367
But if we can entice someone
to pay us sooner,

459
00:18:47,419 --> 00:18:49,387
we can get that revenue in
under the window.

460
00:18:49,471 --> 00:18:51,038
Bad faith--
I like it.

461
00:18:51,089 --> 00:18:52,930
The question is,
who still owes us enough money

462
00:18:53,008 --> 00:18:54,374
to make a difference?

463
00:18:54,426 --> 00:18:55,542
Folsom Foods.

464
00:18:55,594 --> 00:18:56,877
The second they pay
their settlement,

465
00:18:56,928 --> 00:18:58,095
we get paid our fee.

466
00:18:58,180 --> 00:18:59,563
You came to that
all on your own.

467
00:18:59,648 --> 00:19:02,349
Yeah, about an hour ago.
Don't tell me I beat you to it.

468
00:19:02,401 --> 00:19:04,401
Maybe. But you didn't have
Harvey slowing you down.

469
00:19:04,403 --> 00:19:06,270
- That's a fair point.
- Okay, I'm right here.

470
00:19:06,354 --> 00:19:08,055
Well, your idea is no good,

471
00:19:08,106 --> 00:19:09,573
because it'll be
a cold day in hell

472
00:19:09,658 --> 00:19:12,109
before Daniel Hardman lifts
a finger to help this firm,

473
00:19:12,194 --> 00:19:14,278
and I'd rather lose
this negotiation

474
00:19:14,362 --> 00:19:16,082
than to cut a deal
with that son of a bitch.

475
00:19:16,164 --> 00:19:18,232
You don't have to.
Hardman was running point.

476
00:19:18,283 --> 00:19:20,901
Folsom's not his client.
They're Robert Zane's.

477
00:19:20,952 --> 00:19:23,537
- He's no fan of us either.
- Maybe not.

478
00:19:23,588 --> 00:19:27,124
But we can handle
Robert Zane.

479
00:19:29,261 --> 00:19:31,245
You caught on
to my plan there.

480
00:19:31,296 --> 00:19:33,247
You mean the most obvious
plan in the world?

481
00:19:33,298 --> 00:19:35,378
I mean the plan that
I thought of and that you didn't

482
00:19:35,383 --> 00:19:37,251
and that I'm the perfect
person to implement.

483
00:19:37,302 --> 00:19:39,353
You really think
you can handle Robert Zane?

484
00:19:39,420 --> 00:19:40,721
I have a relationship
with him.

485
00:19:40,772 --> 00:19:42,089
Yeah. You're sleeping
with his daughter.

486
00:19:42,140 --> 00:19:43,607
I'm sure
he's your biggest fan.

487
00:19:43,692 --> 00:19:46,777
Okay, it's not like that.
I had dinner at the man's house.

488
00:19:46,862 --> 00:19:48,145
I had dinner
at the White House.

489
00:19:48,230 --> 00:19:49,763
They're not gonna make me
Attorney General.

490
00:19:49,815 --> 00:19:51,431
Okay, first of all,
bullshit.

491
00:19:51,483 --> 00:19:53,084
Second of all,
do you have a better idea?

492
00:19:53,118 --> 00:19:54,434
No, I don't.

493
00:19:54,486 --> 00:19:56,370
But are you ready to use
your relationship with Rachel

494
00:19:56,437 --> 00:19:57,788
to get her father to turn?

495
00:19:57,873 --> 00:19:59,790
Doesn't matter,
because I'm not gonna do that.

496
00:19:59,875 --> 00:20:01,909
I'm just gonna use it
to get him to hear me out

497
00:20:01,960 --> 00:20:04,662
in the first place.
Good luck with that.

498
00:20:04,746 --> 00:20:08,666
Hey, how'd you know that
White House thing was bullshit?

499
00:20:16,341 --> 00:20:19,126
Mike. I was wondering when
I was gonna get you out here.

500
00:20:19,177 --> 00:20:20,460
Ah, golf isn't really
