came to me and asked,

749
00:31:02,675 --> 00:31:04,226
and I think
it's good business.

750
00:31:04,310 --> 00:31:05,550
Well, your idea
of good business

751
00:31:05,561 --> 00:31:06,878
is different from mine,

752
00:31:06,929 --> 00:31:09,514
because we already took
less money from Folsom Foods,

753
00:31:09,565 --> 00:31:11,650
and now you want us to take
less money from Darby.

754
00:31:11,717 --> 00:31:14,219
Jessica,
if we screw him over,

755
00:31:14,270 --> 00:31:15,904
he's gonna come back at us.

756
00:31:15,988 --> 00:31:17,222
It might not be tomorrow.

757
00:31:17,273 --> 00:31:18,774
It might not be six months
from now,

758
00:31:18,858 --> 00:31:20,525
but he's gonna find a way.

759
00:31:20,576 --> 00:31:22,778
- You mean she'll find a way.
- That's exactly what I mean.

760
00:31:22,862 --> 00:31:24,413
And maybe she will.

761
00:31:24,497 --> 00:31:26,731
But I've never known you
to run from a fight before.

762
00:31:26,783 --> 00:31:28,733
My name was never
on the door before.

763
00:31:28,785 --> 00:31:30,869
You said it yourself.

764
00:31:30,920 --> 00:31:34,206
I have to think differently
now that I'm in this position.

765
00:31:34,257 --> 00:31:35,907
I did say that.

766
00:31:35,958 --> 00:31:37,426
And it's not just gonna
be one fight.

767
00:31:37,510 --> 00:31:40,178
It's gonna be the Hatfields
and the McCoys all over again.

768
00:31:40,246 --> 00:31:43,415
Are you sure this isn't really
about your history with her?

769
00:31:43,466 --> 00:31:46,635
- What if it is?
- She could just be playing us.

770
00:31:46,719 --> 00:31:50,088
She could, but...
I trust her.

771
00:31:51,557 --> 00:31:53,591
Jessica,
it's time to turn the page.

772
00:31:56,446 --> 00:31:58,480
Well, I don't want
to turn the page.

773
00:31:58,564 --> 00:32:01,066
I want to close the book.

774
00:32:01,117 --> 00:32:04,769
Tell her we'll exclude
the payment and honor our deal.

775
00:32:10,326 --> 00:32:13,295
Louis, I know it didn't go
exactly as planned,

776
00:32:13,379 --> 00:32:16,331
but you need to pick yourself up
and dust yourself off.

777
00:32:16,416 --> 00:32:18,116
Exactly as planned?

778
00:32:18,167 --> 00:32:20,335
I utterly failed.

779
00:32:20,420 --> 00:32:22,287
I don't even deserve
this stupid mug.

780
00:32:22,338 --> 00:32:24,089
"Litt Up"?
It should say "shit up."

781
00:32:24,140 --> 00:32:25,640
You didn't fail.
You impressed him.

782
00:32:25,725 --> 00:32:28,844
Yeah, that and $45 will get
my cat a Brazilian bikini wax.

783
00:32:28,928 --> 00:32:30,178
You got a new cat?

784
00:32:30,263 --> 00:32:31,796
Fostering.

785
00:32:31,848 --> 00:32:33,899
Louis...enough.

786
00:32:33,966 --> 00:32:36,435
You need to go to Harvey.

787
00:32:36,486 --> 00:32:38,987
You mean tell him that I'm
even more of an embarrassment

788
00:32:39,071 --> 00:32:40,638
than he says I am?

789
00:32:40,690 --> 00:32:42,441
You're not an embarrassment.

790
00:32:42,492 --> 00:32:44,443
You may need Harvey
to put the ball in the end zone,

791
00:32:44,494 --> 00:32:46,027
but you had the idea,
you set it up,

792
00:32:46,112 --> 00:32:48,480
and you drove the ball
down to the one-yard line.

793
00:32:48,531 --> 00:32:50,365
No, I didn't have the idea.

794
00:32:50,450 --> 00:32:51,867
You had the idea!

795
00:32:51,951 --> 00:32:53,919
And you executed it.

796
00:32:53,986 --> 00:32:55,537
But you're giving me credit.

797
00:32:55,621 --> 00:32:57,822
If Harvey executes this,
he'll give you credit.

798
00:32:57,874 --> 00:32:59,508
No, he won't.
He never does.

799
00:32:59,592 --> 00:33:01,209
Louis, he might.

800
00:33:01,294 --> 00:33:03,512
You want him to see
a different side of you,

801
00:33:03,596 --> 00:33:05,663
give him a chance to show
a different side of him.

802
00:33:05,715 --> 00:33:07,549
You know what?
It doesn't matter anyway.

803
00:33:07,633 --> 00:33:09,468
Harvey doesn't need
my help anymore.

804
00:33:09,519 --> 00:33:11,336
It's too late.
No, it isn't.

805
00:33:11,387 --> 00:33:13,138
Haven't you heard?

806
00:33:13,189 --> 00:33:15,390
Heard what?

807
00:33:31,524 --> 00:33:33,375
Harvey,
I have some bad news.

808
00:33:33,459 --> 00:33:35,577
- What is it?
- I think you should sit down.

809
00:33:35,661 --> 00:33:38,046
Donna, unless someone died,
I don't need to sit down.

810
00:33:38,130 --> 00:33:41,383
Just tell me.
Hessington Oil just fired us.

811
00:33:48,474 --> 00:33:50,709
- Scottie betrayed me.
- You don't know that.

812
00:33:50,776 --> 00:33:52,844
One plus one equals two,
Donna.

813
00:33:52,895 --> 00:33:54,563
And I know
how to goddamn add.

814
00:33:54,647 --> 00:33:55,897
I didn't count
the Folsom money,

815
00:33:55,982 --> 00:33:58,066
and suddenly
our oil revenues are gone

816
00:33:58,150 --> 00:34:00,235
and her piece of the pie
just skyrocketed.

817
00:34:00,319 --> 00:34:02,220
Harvey, please,
don't do anything rash.

818
00:34:02,271 --> 00:34:04,222
What the hell
are you saying?

819
00:34:04,273 --> 00:34:06,441
- I'm saying call her.
- How would that go?

820
00:34:06,526 --> 00:34:08,243
"Hey, Scottie,
thanks for dicking me over.

821
00:34:08,327 --> 00:34:09,578
Could you please
take it back?"

822
00:34:09,662 --> 00:34:11,196
You don't know
how it would go.

823
00:34:11,247 --> 00:34:13,415
And you could find out
if you would drop your pride

824
00:34:13,499 --> 00:34:15,179
and just give her
the benefit of the doubt.

825
00:34:15,201 --> 00:34:17,235
You gave someone
the benefit of the doubt,

826
00:34:17,286 --> 00:34:18,837
and look how that turned out.

827
00:34:20,840 --> 00:34:23,041
You think just because
you bought me a handbag,

828
00:34:23,092 --> 00:34:26,011
you can say that to me?

829
00:34:26,078 --> 00:34:27,712
Okay, I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have said that.

830
00:34:27,763 --> 00:34:29,297
But I just got played,

831
00:34:29,382 --> 00:34:32,133
and I'm not about to call
Scottie and cry about it.

832
00:34:32,218 --> 00:34:34,219
- So what are you gonna do?
- I'm gonna figure out

833
00:34:34,270 --> 00:34:36,805
how to do to her
what she just did to me.

834
00:34:44,937 --> 00:34:46,058
- Harvey.
- Not now, Louis.

835
00:34:46,138 --> 00:34:47,590
Yes, now, Harvey.
I've got the answer.

836
00:34:47,591 --> 00:34:48,912
- The answer to what?
- To shoving

837
00:34:48,959 --> 00:34:50,927
the Hessington Oil firing
up Edward Darby's ass.

838
00:34:51,514 --> 00:34:52,881
Harvey.

839
00:34:52,932 --> 00:34:54,582
Harvey!

840
00:34:56,085 --> 00:34:57,853
Tony Gianopolous.

841
00:34:57,920 --> 00:35:00,522
He can triple the revenue
we lost with Hessington Oil.

842
00:35:00,589 --> 00:35:02,924
And they're technically
not a new client.

843
00:35:02,976 --> 00:35:04,943
So there's nothing
Scottie can do.

844
00:35:05,028 --> 00:35:06,445
Well, what makes you think
he's gonna go for it?

845
00:35:06,529 --> 00:35:08,930
Because I went there,
and they are primed to say yes.

846
00:35:08,982 --> 00:35:11,783
They just won't...

847
00:35:11,868 --> 00:35:14,736
They just won't
say yes to me.

848
00:35:14,787 --> 00:35:18,156
Give him this.
They'll say yes to you.

849
00:35:23,663 --> 00:35:25,580
Louis, this is brilliant.

850
00:35:25,632 --> 00:35:28,250
And if you hadn't had the balls
to come to me,

851
00:35:28,301 --> 00:35:29,751
we'd have nothing
right now.

852
00:35:29,802 --> 00:35:31,219
Harvey, no.

853
00:35:31,287 --> 00:35:32,671
I should have come
to you sooner,

854
00:35:32,755 --> 00:35:34,622
but I didn't because I just--
Louis.

855
00:35:34,674 --> 00:35:36,425
I've told you this before,

856
00:35:36,476 --> 00:35:39,127
but it's always been when
I needed something from you.

857
00:35:39,178 --> 00:35:41,963
And I don't need anything
from you right now,

858
00:35:42,015 --> 00:35:43,465
because you just gave it to me.

859
00:35:43,516 --> 00:35:46,935
So maybe you can hear it
when I say it--

860
00:35:46,986 --> 00:35:50,272
I respect you.

861
00:35:50,323 --> 00:35:52,140
You're an excellent attorney,

862
00:35:52,191 --> 00:35:55,027
a valuable member
of this firm.

863
00:35:57,246 --> 00:35:58,497
And a friend?

864
00:35:58,581 --> 00:36:00,315
Don't push it.

865
00:36:02,035 --> 00:36:03,485
Sorry.

866
00:36:03,536 --> 00:36:07,372
Seriously, Harvey,
I just have to say, um...

867
00:36:09,375 --> 00:36:11,460
It means so much
when you say all that.

868
00:36:11,511 --> 00:36:12,878
Do you need a tissue
or something?

869
00:36:12,962 --> 00:36:15,013
- Can I use your pocket square?
- Under no circumstances.

870
00:36:15,098 --> 00:36:17,432
I'll be fine.
And you and Jessica

871
00:36:17,500 --> 00:36:19,851
need to take that over
to Gianopolous right now.

872
00:36:19,936 --> 00:36:22,837
Screw that.
I'm going over there with you.

873
00:36:29,812 --> 00:36:31,229
He's not there.

874
00:36:31,314 --> 00:36:32,481
What?
Where is he?

875
00:36:32,532 --> 00:36:34,682
He went to see
Tony Gianopolous.

876
00:36:34,734 --> 00:36:36,735
- By himself?
- No, with Louis.

877
00:36:36,819 --> 00:36:38,987
With Louis?
What, is he mad at me?

878
00:36:39,038 --> 00:36:41,039
Rachel's the only one
who's mad at you.

879
00:36:42,691 --> 00:36:43,909
- She told you.
- She didn't have to.

880
00:36:43,993 --> 00:36:45,410
What were you thinking,

881
00:36:45,495 --> 00:36:46,878
pulling all that shit
with her dad?

882
00:36:46,963 --> 00:36:48,547
I didn't think
it would come to that.

883
00:36:48,631 --> 00:36:50,082
He didn't mind.
Why should she?

884
00:36:51,417 --> 00:36:53,585
Anyone who understands women
in any way

885
00:36:53,669 --> 00:36:55,887
would know that was
a bad idea from the start.

886
00:36:55,972 --> 00:36:58,056
- Harvey liked it.
- Proving my point.

887
00:37:01,427 --> 00:37:03,061
I asked her
to move in with me.

888
00:37:03,146 --> 00:37:04,379
I know.

889
00:37:04,430 --> 00:37:05,547
She told you?

890
00:37:05,598 --> 00:37:07,048
Of course she did.

891
00:37:07,100 --> 00:37:09,217
I can't intuit everything.
What am I, the Dalai Lama?

892
00:37:09,268 --> 00:37:11,436
Donna, you should have seen
her face when I asked her.

893
00:37:11,521 --> 00:37:13,522
She was so happy.

894
00:37:13,573 --> 00:37:15,223
I'm sure she was.
It was very romantic.

895
00:37:15,274 --> 00:37:17,442
How could she be so happy
and then just not want to do it?

896
00:37:17,527 --> 00:37:19,894
Who says
she doesn't want to do it?

897
00:37:19,946 --> 00:37:21,729
I told her to take her time,

898
00:37:21,781 --> 00:37:23,731
but I-I didn't think
she'd need it.

899
00:37:23,783 --> 00:37:25,584
Why wouldn't she need it?

900
00:37:25,668 --> 00:37:27,669
Just because you made
some romantic gesture

901
00:37:27,736 --> 00:37:29,921
doesn't mean that all reason
goes out the window.

902
00:37:30,006 --> 00:37:31,673
I've had a pit in my stomach
since last night.

903
00:37:31,740 --> 00:37:33,175
I...

904
00:37:33,242 --> 00:37:35,210
I need to do something.

905
00:37:35,261 --> 00:37:37,745
You need to look
in the mirror.

906
00:37:37,797 --> 00:37:39,214
What?

907
00:37:40,516 --> 00:37:42,236
I just jumped into
a relationship with a man

908
00:37:42,268 --> 00:37:43,602
who, it turns out,

909
00:37:43,686 --> 00:37:45,437
was pretending to be
something he wasn't.

910
00:37:45,521 --> 00:37:46,938
Rachel already knows

911
00:37:47,023 --> 00:37:49,608
that you're pretending to be
something you're not.

912
00:37:49,692 --> 00:37:51,443
All you need to do
is just give her time

913
00:37:51,527 --> 00:37:52,927
to figure it all out.

914
00:37:54,564 --> 00:37:56,865
What if she says no?

915
00:37:56,932 --> 00:37:58,817
Then she says no.

916
00:37:58,901 --> 00:38:02,537
But pushing her isn't going
to stop that from happening.

917
00:38:07,243 --> 00:38:09,123
If you're here to complain
about Hessington Oil,

918
00:38:09,128 --> 00:38:10,328
I had nothing to do with it.

919
00:38:10,413 --> 00:38:11,580
I'm just
the majority shareholder.

920
00:38:11,631 --> 00:38:13,799
I don't get involved
in day-to-day stuff.

921
00:38:13,883 --> 00:38:16,334
- We're not here to complain.
- We're here to bring a gift.

922
00:38:16,419 --> 00:38:17,969
The question is,
what do you get a man

923
00:38:18,054 --> 00:38:19,838
who can burn a $50,000 bond?

924
00:38:19,922 --> 00:38:22,474
Something money can't buy.

925
00:38:25,094 --> 00:38:27,462
- This isn't public.
- It will be in 48 hours.

926
00:38:27,513 --> 00:38:29,797
And it's legal now.
How do you know that?

927
00:38:29,849 --> 00:38:31,316
Because I structured it
that way.

928
00:38:31,400 --> 00:38:34,102
I can do more of the same
for you, but he didn't tell you,

929
00:38:34,153 --> 00:38:36,137
because I wasn't enough
of a name.

930
00:38:36,189 --> 00:38:38,440
- You're not.
- But I am.

931
00:38:38,491 --> 00:38:40,975
Well, you are, as a man
who shoots from the hip,

932
00:38:41,027 --> 00:38:42,160
which I like, but--

933
00:38:42,245 --> 00:38:44,112
You also need
a stabilizing influence.

934
00:38:44,163 --> 00:38:46,865
- Not a football player.
- But a fan of the ballet.

935
00:38:46,949 --> 00:38:49,034
- Muscle.
- And finesse.

936
00:38:49,118 --> 00:38:51,253
And you guys think
that I'm not aware

937
00:38:51,320 --> 00:38:53,371
that this is all
about your merger negotiations.

938
00:38:53,456 --> 00:38:54,756
Oh, I was counting on you
being aware of it.

939
00:38:54,823 --> 00:38:56,007
Because then
you'll also be aware

940
00:38:56,092 --> 00:38:57,459
that we can be very flexible
in our billings.

941
00:38:57,510 --> 00:38:59,177
As long as I pay
enough up front

942
00:38:59,262 --> 00:39:00,929
to tip the scales
in your favor.

943
00:39:00,996 --> 00:39:02,464
We'll structure
a schedule that results

944
00:39:02,515 --> 00:39:04,165
in you getting a substantial
financial benefit.

945
00:39:04,217 --> 00:39:05,800
Which is his specialty.

946
00:39:05,852 --> 00:39:07,302
Go ahead.
Tell him.

947
00:39:07,353 --> 00:39:09,271
He's a badass.

948
00:39:11,357 --> 00:39:13,525
What do you say we celebrate
our new association

949
00:39:13,609 --> 00:39:16,394
over dinner in Chicago
with Michael Jordan?

950
00:39:16,479 --> 00:39:18,196
We can take my private jet.

951
00:39:18,281 --> 00:39:20,198
Hey! Which will allow us
to pay for it

952
00:39:20,283 --> 00:39:21,849
and for you to write it off.

953
00:39:35,248 --> 00:39:37,249
Hey.

954
00:39:37,333 --> 00:39:38,700
Hey.

955
00:39:38,751 --> 00:39:40,752
I know you're probably
busy...

956
00:39:40,836 --> 00:39:42,504
I'm actually not.

957
00:39:49,845 --> 00:39:52,213
Rachel, I...

958
00:39:52,265 --> 00:39:54,015
I know that dating me
is complicated--

959
00:39:54,066 --> 00:39:55,517
- Mike--
- I just--

960
00:39:57,720 --> 00:40:00,855
I just want you to know you can
take as much time as you need.

961
00:40:03,743 --> 00:40:06,194
I love you.

962
00:40:09,665 --> 00:40:11,666
I love you too.

963
00:40:17,173 --> 00:40:19,907
I got into Stanford.

964
00:40:30,386 --> 00:40:33,271
What the hell
is wrong with you?

965
00:40:33,356 --> 00:40:35,256
I see you got
my little gut punch.

966
00:40:35,308 --> 00:40:37,759
I came to you hat in hand,
and this is what you do--

967
00:40:37,810 --> 00:40:39,394
stack the numbers?
- Hat in hand?

968
00:40:39,445 --> 00:40:41,313
More like a wolf
in sheep's clothing.

969
00:40:41,397 --> 00:40:43,949
- What are you talking about?
- Hessington Oil.

970
00:40:44,033 --> 00:40:45,283
I had nothing
to do with that.

971
00:40:45,368 --> 00:40:47,319
Something dropped
from the sky,

972
00:40:47,403 --> 00:40:48,703
tilted everything
in your favor

973
00:40:48,771 --> 00:40:50,989
right after I cut you a break?
I don't think so.

974
00:40:51,073 --> 00:40:53,658
Harvey, I gave you my word,
and I honored it.

975
00:40:53,743 --> 00:40:55,109
Bullshit.
You're saying saying that

976
00:40:55,161 --> 00:40:56,401
because I've got
the upper hand.

977
00:40:56,412 --> 00:40:57,746
This is not
about the upper hand.

978
00:40:57,797 --> 00:40:59,158
You're always
about the upper hand!

979
00:40:59,165 --> 00:41:00,948
Harvey, stop.

980
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:03,668
I came to you
and asked for mercy.

981
00:41:03,753 --> 00:41:05,670
Do you know how hard
that was for me?

982
00:41:05,755 --> 00:41:08,089
And then for me to turn around
and use that to dupe you--

983
00:41:08,140 --> 00:41:10,091
how could you think
I would do that?

984
00:41:10,142 --> 00:41:11,343
Well, what would you
have thought?

985
00:41:11,427 --> 00:41:13,178
I don't know,
but you could have called me.

986
00:41:13,262 --> 00:41:14,962
- And say what?
- And asked me

987
00:41:15,014 --> 00:41:16,598
to exclude the firing
from the calculations.

988
00:41:16,649 --> 00:41:17,632
I'm not gonna do--

989
00:41:17,683 --> 00:41:19,133
What?
You're not gonna do what?

990
00:41:19,185 --> 00:41:20,825
Not gonna give me
the benefit of the doubt

991
00:41:20,853 --> 00:41:23,571
and be vulnerable--
expose yourself?

992
00:41:23,639 --> 00:41:25,807
I already did that
when I trusted you.

993
00:41:25,858 --> 00:41:29,361
That was mercy, which is
from a position of strength.

994
00:41:29,445 --> 00:41:32,497
Being vulnerable is
